Every now and then you’ll find that you are just stumped with a certain leaf identification adventures. One of the best things you can do is to take a field guide out with you to help with your classification because it’s likely that you’ll find an exact match even if you’ve never seen the tree or its leaves before. A field guide can help walk you through the process of leaf identification on these ones that are tough to identify or may look very similar to other species of trees. Especially when you are first starting, you’ll find that a tree or leaf identification field guide is very helpful. As you gain more knowledge about your area, you’ll find that you are able to make name a tree with the leaves alone more often than not.
<br /><br />
Leaves are to trees like finger prints are to people, while they may all look the same at first glance, when you really start looking you’ll realize that they are all very different. There are different shapes, patterns, and a difference in overall structure. Identifying leaves can be a lot of fun, and you can learn a lot about what most of us take for granted. Tree identification can be done for fun, for science projects, and even as a job if you are so lucky! There is a lot of information in those leaves, so when you find interesting ones don’t be afraid to take them home and really study them and see if you just can’t figure out what type of tree they are from.